full_article:
In an unprecedented step, the Balendra Shah-led government in Nepal has formed a five-member judicial panel to investigate the assets of individuals who held public office from 2006 to the 2025–26 fiscal year. The move marks the widest-ever scrutiny of the country’s post-monarchy political and bureaucratic elite, targeting alleged irregularities in wealth accumulation over nearly two decades.

